# Lyx Project Conventions

## Monorepo Structure

- **packages/** ‚Äî framework packages (`@lyx/types`, `@lyx/sdk`, `@lyx/shell`, `@lyx/cli`, `@lyx/registry`, `@lyx/vite-plugin`)
- **platform/** ‚Äî admin services (`admin-api`, `admin-ui`, `ssr`, `nginx`)
- **apps/** ‚Äî user projects created with `lyx init`
- **scripts/** ‚Äî automation (`platform.sh`, `deploy-aws.sh`, `ensure-infra.sh`)

## CLI is the single source of truth

All MFE operations go through the `lyx` CLI. Never create MFEs manually.

```bash
lyx init <project-name>      # creates apps/<project-name>/
lyx create <mfe> --slot main # creates mfes/<mfe>/ inside the project
lyx deploy                   # builds, versions, uploads MFEs
lyx login -s <url>           # authenticate to a server
```

## AWS Credentials (Local)

Before any AWS command, always check credentials:

```bash
lyx aws status
```

If expired or missing, guide the user to: `lyx aws login`

- Credentials stored in `~/.lyx-aws` (auto-loaded by all Lyx scripts)
- Never hardcode credentials ‚Äî `~/.lyx-aws` is in `.gitignore`
- For MFE deployment (`lyx deploy`): NO AWS credentials needed (talks to Admin API)
- For infrastructure (`deploy-aws.sh`, `ensure-infra.sh`): AWS credentials required

## MFE Rules

1. Every MFE must `export default` a React component from `src/index.tsx`
2. MFE config lives in `mfe.config.json` (name, slot, version)
3. Versions auto-increment on `lyx deploy` ‚Äî never set manually
4. Slots: `root`, `header`, `sidebar`, `main`, `footer`
5. MFEs are independent ‚Äî no direct imports between them
6. Communication via SDK: `emit`/`on` for events, `useSharedState` for shared data

## Code Standards

- Language: TypeScript (strict)
- All user-facing text, comments, docs: **English only**
- **NEVER use `any` or `as any`** ‚Äî see `.cursor/rules/strict-typing.mdc` for alternatives
- Functional React components only ‚Äî no class components
- Use `@lyx/sdk` for inter-MFE communication, never `window` directly
- Error handling: always catch and log, never swallow errors

## Package Manager

- **pnpm** only (workspace-based)
- Run `pnpm install` from the monorepo root after adding dependencies
- Use `pnpm nx run-many -t build` for multi-package builds

## Git

- Branch: `main` is production
- Commits: conventional commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`)
- PR labels: always add `ai` and `cursor`

## Documentation

- `README.md` ‚Äî user-facing guide, always up-to-date
- `docs/features.md` ‚Äî complete feature inventory (SDK, CLI, Shell, API, UI, Infra)
- `docs/errors.md` ‚Äî error knowledge base with cause/fix/prevention
- `docs/architecture.md` ‚Äî system design, data flow, decision records
- `docs/roles.md` ‚Äî 6-role decision framework (PO, PM, Architect, Staff, Dev, QA)
- `docs/backlog.md` ‚Äî product backlog with P0-P3 priorities (owned by PO)
- `docs/competitive-analysis.md` ‚Äî market analysis vs competitors (owned by PO)
- `docs/workplan.md` ‚Äî sprint execution tracking (owned by PM)

## Product Workflow

New features follow the pipeline defined in `.cursor/rules/product-workflow.mdc`:

1. PO analyzes request against competitive landscape
2. PM routes to Architect + Staff for analysis
3. Engineer implements after approval
4. QA validates, docs updated, PO signs off

